SECTION 0 — DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

0.1 "Work" means all software, source code, model code, documentation,
    specifications, datasets, design files, research text, and other
    copyrightable material released by the Licensor under this License.

0.2 "Source Materials" means the files and information reasonably required to
    inspect, reproduce, modify, and verify the Work or a derivative of the
    Work, including source code, build instructions, dependency manifests,
    interface specifications, and associated documentation.

0.3 "Derivative Work" means a work based upon the Work that would be treated
    as a derivative work, adaptation, modification, or other copyright-
    restricted reuse under applicable law.

0.4 "Qualifying Use" means any act beyond passive viewing that exercises,
    enables, or procures exercise of rights reserved to the copyright holder
    in the Work, including downloading, cloning, copying, modifying, training
    on, fine-tuning on, integrating, compiling, executing, distributing,
    sublicensing, offering as a hosted service, embedding in a product, or
    deploying in production.

0.5 "Effective Market Capitalization" means:

    (a) for a public company, the greater of:

        (i)   its closing equity value on the relevant measurement date; and

        (ii)  the average of its closing equity values over the thirty (30)
              trading days ending on the relevant measurement date; and

    (b) for a private company, the greatest of:

        (i)   its most recent arm's-length primary financing valuation;

        (ii)  any valuation adopted in audited financial statements, a board-
              approved fair value determination, a 409A valuation, or an
              equivalent formal valuation prepared within the preceding twenty-
              four (24) months;

        (iii) any valuation implied by a tender offer, secondary sale,
              acquisition offer, convertible security pricing cap, or similar
              financing or liquidity event within the preceding twenty-four
              (24) months; or

        (iv)  other contemporaneous valuation evidence ordinarily relied upon
              in business, finance, or M&A practice; and

    (c) if an entity does not maintain or produce reliable records sufficient
        to determine its valuation, the Licensor may classify that entity using
        any reasonable evidence, and that classification is presumed correct
        unless rebutted by contemporaneous corporate records.

0.6 "Top Entity" means any entity whose Effective Market Capitalization is at
    least $1,000,000,000 USD.

0.7 "Annual License Fee" means the flat annual fee owed by a Top Entity for
    each calendar year in which it makes Qualifying Use of the Work. The
    applicable fee is determined by the entity's Effective Market
    Capitalization tier during that year. For Top Entities, this fee schedule
    is a fixed commercial condition of access to the Work.

    TIERED ANNUAL LICENSE FEE SCHEDULE

    Tier 1 — $1,000,000,000 to $9,999,999,999
        $34,500,000 USD per year

    Tier 2 — $10,000,000,000 to $99,999,999,999
        $275,000,000 USD per year

    Tier 3 — $100,000,000,000 to $499,999,999,999
        $2,900,000,000 USD per year

    Tier 4 — $500,000,000,000 to $999,999,999,999
        $5,175,000,000 USD per year

    Tier 5 — $1,000,000,000,000 to $2,999,999,999,999
        $13,800,000,000 USD per year

    Tier 6 — $3,000,000,000,000 and above
        $24,150,000,000 USD per year

0.8 "Canonical Repository" means the repository located at:
    https://github.com/TimeLordRaps/the-time-license

