SECTION 6 — PAYMENT DESTINATION
================================================================================

6.1 One hundred percent (100%) of all fees, interest, settlements, judgments,
    and other monetary recoveries under this License are payable directly to
    the Licensor personally, for unrestricted use at the Licensor's sole
    discretion.

================================================================================
SECTION 6A — EQUITY ACCEPTANCE AND SOVEREIGN FUND TRANSFER
================================================================================

6A.1 EQUITY AS ALTERNATIVE CONSIDERATION. At the Licensor's sole election,
    the Licensor may accept equity interests, stock, tokens, or other
    ownership instruments in an entity in partial or full satisfaction of any
    Annual License Fee, settlement, judgment, or other monetary obligation
    under this License. No entity is required to offer equity; cash or fiat
    currency remains the default form of payment under Section 3.

6A.2 ANTI-DILUTION PROTECTION. Any equity granted to or accepted by the
    Licensor under this Section carries immediate full-ratchet anti-dilution
    protection, enforceable on all statutorily available equity assignment
    mechanisms. This protection is effective immediately upon grant and
    survives reorganization, merger, stock split, reverse stock split,
    recapitalization, secondary offering, spin-off, and any other corporate
    event that would otherwise reduce the Licensor's proportional ownership
    interest.

6A.3 SOVEREIGN FUND TRANSFER. Equity accepted under this Section is held
    toward a generalized sovereign fund designated and controlled by the
    Licensor. The Licensor may transfer, assign, or contribute any such
    equity to that sovereign fund at any time. The transfer horizon for
    equity held under this Section is one hundred (100) years from the date
    of acceptance, during which the Licensor or the sovereign fund retains
    all rights of ownership, voting, and disposition.

6A.4 NO FORCED EQUITY. Nothing in this Section obligates the Licensor to
    accept equity in lieu of cash. The Licensor may demand cash payment
    under Section 3 at any time, and an entity's offer of equity does not
    discharge a cash obligation unless the Licensor accepts that equity in
    a separate signed writing or by conduct clearly manifesting acceptance.

