SECTION 7 — VERSIONING AND FUTURE USE
================================================================================

7.1 Each published version of this License becomes effective on the date that
    version is first published in the Canonical Repository.

7.2 A later version of this License does not retroactively alter liabilities,
    permissions, or completed acts governed by an earlier version.

7.3 If a party continues Qualifying Use after a later version is published and
    after that party has actual or constructive notice of the later version,
    the later version governs that party's future Qualifying Use from that
    point forward. That party also remains bound by all obligations that
    accrued under prior versions, and any new obligations introduced by the
    later version compound with, rather than replace, those prior obligations.

7.4 Obligations that accrued under an earlier version remain enforceable even
    if a later version is subsequently published.

7.5 Commit history, publication records, and any OpenTimestamp proof associated
    with the License are evidence of publication order and timing, but do not
    by themselves retroactively rewrite prior obligations.

7.6 Obligations under successive versions are cumulative. Each new version may
    introduce additional obligations that compound with, rather than replace,
    obligations from prior versions. A party's total obligations are the union
    of all obligations from every version under which it made or continued
    Qualifying Use.

